00:05:37.294 --> 00:05:38.770
OK, So here is the deal.

00:05:38.970 --> 00:05:42.559
Once Dr. Symonds has done all the mathematics,
it comes down to this.

00:05:42.759 --> 00:05:49.321
The base thing to do is to look inside
37 percent of the toilets.

00:05:49.521 --> 00:05:53.121
And after you hit that 37 percent
tipping point,

00:05:53.321 --> 00:05:58.477
you choose the first toilet after that
that's better than everything that came before.

00:05:58.677 --> 00:06:03.161
That gives you the best chance
of ending up in the best toilet.

00:06:03.361 --> 00:06:06.340
That doesn't mean you can skip that
first 37 percent.

00:06:06.540 --> 00:06:08.428
You've actually got to look inside
them unfortunately,

00:06:08.628 --> 00:06:13.460
so that you can make the comparison
after you've gone past the tipping point,

00:06:13.660 --> 00:06:16.205
after you've gone past that
37 percent.

00:06:16.405 --> 00:06:21.082
To make it really simple
imagine Glastonbury, imagine a 100 toilets.

00:06:21.282 --> 00:06:25.175
You got to look inside 37,
and after the 37th

00:06:25.375 --> 00:06:29.880
pick the first one after that,
that's better than what came before.

00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:33.051
Dr. Symonds: So we've used the example
of choosing the best toilet,

00:06:33.251 --> 00:06:36.897
but this a famous mathematical problem
that you may have seen before

00:06:37.097 --> 00:06:38.020
in a different context.

00:06:38.220 --> 00:06:41.335
You may have heard of it before
called "The Secretary Problem",

00:06:41.535 --> 00:06:42.873
which is the same process.

00:06:43.073 --> 00:06:47.055
This time you want to find
the best secretary for the job,

00:06:47.255 --> 00:06:50.105
but you were going to interview
an n number of people,

00:06:50.305 --> 00:06:51.717
say maybe a 100 people.

00:06:51.917 --> 00:06:56.699
You can only accept or reject each secretary
once they've been interviewed.

00:06:56.899 --> 00:07:00.770
So when do you stop interviewing
those secretaries

00:07:00.970 --> 00:07:04.838
and start accepting one of them
hoping that you have the best for the job?

00:07:05.038 --> 00:07:08.525
Or another famous use of this
is in the dating world.

00:07:08.725 --> 00:07:12.000
If you want to find the best partner,
your soul mate out there,

00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:16.511
then how many people should you date
before you should start accepting

00:07:16.711 --> 00:07:18.935
and settling down with that
next person

00:07:19.135 --> 00:07:22.058
and hoping that that is the person
you're supposed to be with

00:07:22.258 --> 00:07:23.478
for the rest of your life.

